definition.value: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 20 carbons and 2 double bonds.

A  5-methyl-5-(4-phenoxyphenyl)-3-(phenylamino)-1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione that is the (active) (S)-enantiomer of famoxadone. It prevents spore germination and mycelial growth of sensitive fungi and is used in agriculture for the control of various fungal diseases.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 22 carbons and 3 double bonds.
